Description of included files:
lab0.c - the single C source module that compiles cleanly
Makefile - the... makefile, as described in the spec
    supports: $make, $make dist, $make check, $make clean
backtrace.png - screenshot of segfault and assoc. stack-trace
breakpoint - screenshot of breakpoint and var. inspection
README - identification, descr. of files, descr. of smoke-test, references

Brief description of smoke-test cases:
1 data_comparison:
checks if the command '$./lab0 --input=input.txt --output=output.txt' faithfully
copies the contents of the input file into the output file
2 segfault:
checks if the command '$./lab0 --segfault' actually segmentation faults
3 catch:
checks if the command '$./lab0 --segfault' actually catches segmentation faults
4 unreadable:
checks if the command '$./lab0 --input=input.txt --output=output.txt' deals with
unreadable input files in a correct way
5 unwritable:
checks if the command '$./lab0 --input=input.txt --output=output.txt' deals with
unwritable output files in a correct way

